衍生化石；移积化石；转生化石
化石显示；化石记录；化石证据

bilingual.source: Fossil fuels are harmful to the environment.
This fossil is millions of years old.
bilingual.target: 这个化石有数百万年的历史。
这个化石包含了完整的头骨。

bilingual.source: I saw a dinosaur fossil in the museum.
bilingual.target: 我在博物馆里看到了恐龙的化石。

bilingual.source: The energy from fossil fuels is exhaustible.
bilingual.target: 化石燃料的能量是可耗尽的。

bilingual.source: This fossil shows the centrum of a dinosaur.
bilingual.target: 这个化石显示了恐龙的椎体。

bilingual.source: I saw a pterosaur fossil in the museum.
bilingual.target: 我在博物馆里看到了一个飞龙的化石。

bilingual.source: They found a rare fossil in the desert.
bilingual.target: 他们在沙漠中发现了一个罕见的化石。
燃烧化石燃料会产生二氧化硫。

list.abstract: fossil，始建于1984年，专注于时尚配件的品牌，隶属美国纳斯达克上市公司。 fossil在全球90多个国家拥有超过390家门店，产品包括手表、包袋、首饰等。 旗下的品牌FOSSIL，RELIC，MICHELE，ZODIAC，Skagen Denmark拥有广泛的时尚配饰。

yingyinNormal.en: What's a fossil? A fossil is the remains of an animal that lived long ago when there were dinosaurs. Dinosaur.
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么是化石？所谓化石呢就是很久以前的动物死了之后的遗体，比方说恐龙时代。恐龙！

yingyinNormal.en: Oh. Peppa's right. That's not a shell. George has found a fossil.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩奇说得对，那不是海螺。乔治找到的是一块化石。

yingyinNormal.en: At least 99.9% of creatures that have ever lived aren't preserved in the fossil record.
yingyinNormal.zh: 至少99.9%曾经存在过的生物没能成为化石。

yingyinNormal.en: Fossil energy, the oil we need for our civilization, is causing the ocean to overheat.
yingyinNormal.zh: 化石能源，用来发展文明的石油，使海洋温度升得过高。

yingyinNormal.en: There are many ways to become a fossil, so let's highlight your top death options.
yingyinNormal.zh: 变成化石的方式有很多，我们着重聊聊那些高端一些的死法。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, what is in here? Rocks? No-no, this is my collection of fossil samples. So, rocks.
yingyinNormal.zh: 里面是什么？石头吗？不，我收集的化石样本。就是石头嘛。

yingyinNormal.en: But it was all worth it because you're a famous fossil! Now, you better hold that pose!
yingyinNormal.zh: 当这一切都值得因为你成了著名的化石！现在，最好保持那个姿势！

yingyinNormal.en: She whacks away at layers of rock above you or spots your fossil exposed in a creek bank after a flood.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她打碎你上面的层层岩石或者在河边经过一场洪水后你化石的一部分露出来。

yingyinNormal.en: Over time, the sediments around your fossil will lithify or turn into rock. But you're not in the clear yet!
yingyinNormal.zh: 久而久之，你身体化石周围的沉积物将岩石化或者变成岩石。但你还不是不能放心！

yingyinNormal.en: To provide the energy needed to power China's growth means supply the nation's power plants with vast quantities of fossil fuels.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为中华崛起提供所需的能量，意味着给这个国家的发电站提供大量的化石燃料。

yingyinNormal.en: If you want your corpse in the exclusive 0.01% Club, the Hall of Preserved Fossil Fame, it will not be easy. You better work!
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你想要你的遗骨成为那0.01%，进入名人化石保存室，并不容易。你最好努力！

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, did Monica and Chandler take off yet? Yeah. Damn. They left without my pass to the Nassau Fossil and Natural History Museum.
yingyinNormal.zh: 莫妮卡跟钱德出发了吗？对。该死，他们没有带纳索化石与天然历史博物馆的通行证。

yingyinNormal.en: But looking at the fossil record, knowing what I know about this infection, you cannot say for certain it isn't what killed off the dinosaurs.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是看看化石记录，加上我对感染的了解，你不能完全否认当初灭绝恐龙的就是这东西。

yingyinNormal.en: Imagine being a fossil: touring the world's great museums, inspiring awe in onlookers of all ages, posing for hordes of fawning photographers.
yingyinNormal.zh: 想象自己若成为化石：在世界各大博物馆之间游走，使各年龄层的游客们都心怀敬畏，在大批殷勤的摄影师面前摆造型。

yingyinNormal.en: They could get uplifted into a mountain range and eroded away or carried along in an oceanic plate and subducted back into the Earth's mantle, melting your fossil into hot mush.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们可能因为地壳上升成为山脉又被侵蚀流失或是随着大洋板块潜没又进入地幔，将你的化石熔化。

yingyinNormal.en: Generally, the right place to be if you want to end up a fossil is wherever sediment is actively being deposited, like a lake or an ocean floor. A mountaintop or prairie? Not good!
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你想成为化石，一般来讲，最好的地方是沉积物容易保存的地方，像湖底或海底。山顶或大草原？不靠谱！

yingyinNormal.en: For decades, nuclear and coal have been the traditional stable workhorses that power the grid, but we're increasingly turning to a fossil fuel that's seen as both safer and cleaner, natural gas.
yingyinNormal.zh: 近几十年,核能和煤炭已经成为传统的稳定能源，但我们逐渐开始使用化石燃料，这被认为是更安全更清洁的能源，天然气。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Fossil</highlight> fuels — coal, oil, gas — still generate roughly 85 percent of the world's energy supply.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 化石燃料--煤、石油、天然气--仍占世界能源供应的大约85%。

examination_example.sentence: President Trump has underlined <highlight>fossil</highlight> fuels — especially coal — as the path to economic growth.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 特朗普总统强调将化石燃料--尤其是煤炭--作为经济增长的途径。

sense_info_list.en: the remains (or an impression) of a plant or animal that existed in a past geological age and that has been excavated from the soil

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>fossil</highlight> record shows that many species have endured for millions of years — so why shouldn't we?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 化石记录显示，许多物种已经存活了数百万年——那么我们为什么不能呢？
